      • getAllItemSimpleOutputsFromInventory

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> getAllItemSimpleOutputsFromInventory​(java.lang.String type)
        Returns all of the simple outputs from all items of the given type in the player's inventory.

        If the type is null or "all", then the method returns simple outputs of all items in the player's inventory.

        Parameters:
        type - The type of the item. If null is given, then searches for all types.
        Returns:
        All of the item simple outputs of the given type in the player's inventory all put into one ArrayList.

      • getOutputByNameAndType

        public static java.lang.String getOutputByNameAndType​(java.lang.String name,
                                                      java.lang.String type)
        Returns the output of an item with the given name and type from TextFighter's item arraylists.

        If name or type is null, return null.

        Note that there is no equivalent method for getting from the inventory because item values do not change after they are cloned to it.

        Parameters:
        name - The name of the item. If null is given, then returns null.
        type - The type of the item. If null is given, then returns null.
        Returns:
        output of an item with the given name and type from TextFighter's item arraylists. If name or type is null, return null.

      • movePlayer

        public static boolean movePlayer​(java.lang.String location)
        moves the player to a new location.

        If the given location name is null, then return false (signaling failure). If a location with the name given does not exist, return false (signaling failure).

        the game invokes all possible postmethods of the previous location, sets the new location, then invokes the possible premethods of the new location.

        Parameters:
        location - The name of the location.
        Returns:
        Whether or not the move was successful.
